description: {"blocks":[{"key":"bev0g","text":"SuperTEV is a mutated version of TEV (Tobacco Etch Protease) a cysteine protease widely used in labs as it is highly specific to a cleavage sequence that can be genetically encoded. Depending on the lab, it has been reported that the protease is unstable or purifies with low yields. Efforts have been made for many years (Tropea, 2009, Methods Mol Biol) to improve its solubility. Here we report our platform's efforts in generating a new TEV variant, called SuperTEV, that incorporates 9 mutations identified by different groups in recent years applied together at once. We find that the protein is easily produced and purified in large amounts and is functional. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9vjsh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8cnmb","text":"The list of mutations on the canonical TEV protease are the following (with references that also identified the same mutations):","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7s65e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1fhse","text":"T17S (directed evolution, increased solubility and production) van den Berg et al., 2006 and Wei et al., 2012","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"82nde","text":"L56V (rational design, improved solubility) Cabrita et al., 2007 and Wei et al., 2012","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7v5v6","text":"N68D (directed evolution, increased solubility and production) van den Berg et al., 2006 and Wei et al., 2012","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"801a","text":"I77V (directed evolution, increased solubility and production) van den Berg et al., 2006 and Wei et al., 2012","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9u9oi","text":"S135G (rational design, increased solubility) Cabrita et al., 2007 and Wei et al., 2012","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5hmdn","text":"I138T (increased catalytic activity;
